-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Acknowledgments
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------

These scripts are designed to run within PixInsight (https://pixinsight.com/), a commercial image
processing platform developed by Pleiades Astrophoto S.L. This product is based on software
from the PixInsight project, developed by Pleiades Astrophoto and its contributors
(https://pixinsight.com/).

Part 1 — Lazy Workflow Part 1

ASTAP plate solving uses the ASTAP command-line interface (https://www.hnsky.org/astap.htm)
by Han Kleijn, licensed under the Mozilla Public License 2.0 (https://mozilla.org/MPL/2.0/).
ASTAP is not included and must be separately installed. ASTAP integration approach inspired by
BlindSolver2000 by Franklin Marek (www.setiastro.com), licensed under CC BY-NC 4.0
(http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/).

ImageSolver by (C) 2012-2024 Andrés del Pozo / (C) 2019-2024 Juan Conejero (PTeam).

Standard PixInsight processes called by this script: SpectroPhotometricFluxCalibration,
MultiscaleGradientCorrection, GradientCorrection, and DynamicBackgroundExtraction.

Part 2 — Lazy Workflow Part 2

Adaptive Auto STF algorithm based on PixInsight's standard Screen Transfer Function
methodology by Juan Conejero / Pleiades Astrophoto.

Background finder concept inspired by FindBackground by Gerrit Erdt and Franklin Marek
(SetiAstro), licensed under CC BY-NC 4.0 (http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/). Our
implementation is independently written with a different algorithm and scoring approach.

Standard PixInsight processes called by this script: SpectrophotometricColorCalibration (SPCC),
BackgroundNeutralization, ColorCalibration.

